data.description: Divorce forces sale, Get a jump on this now and beat the spring rush. It's on the way up to Animal Hill, no manufactured allowed, 2448 sq ft 4br 3 bath 2 story, 2 car insulated heated garage, large lot,  tons of parking on a circular driveway, full 50 amp RV hookups with sewer hookup, game room (I currently use for my large golf swing training setup, and workout equipment), Jacuzzi in the house in its own room with skylights and view of the backyard canyon, large laundry/pantry room, granite countertops matching kitchen and bathrooms, wood burning stove that heats the ENTIRE house, wall heaters in every room, new roof 2 years ago, crawl space is an unfinished basement at 6ft tall x 300 sq ft, amazing views, front and back decks, lots of parking, partial fenced yard and fenced dog run. We live in it full time and its move in ready.  Its furnished now and items inside are fully negotiable (save me the trouble of moving them) if you are serious we can meet and talk more, the lesser house across the street sold this year for over a million so I'm not going to deal with low-ballers.  We are talking size, location and a way into this market before it lists, if you know Munds Park you know what I mean. The pics are from the deck and kitchen, I have hundreds more, never miss a sunset.
data.whatILove: The size, the amenities, the views, the functionality, the location, the potential,  What's not to love?
